        <title>Data Management Plan</title>
        <description>To achieve the research objectives open science practices will be implemented Articles for publication arising from the project will be proposed to peerreviewed Gold Open Access journals under CC BY license Preference will be given to journals which accept preprints Indeed the early and open sharing of knowledge through the deposit of the preprint on the Zenodo server and the peer review process will stimulate debate within the scientific community and suggestions could be accepted before the final publication The final research products will be available in open access as well in the institutional repository of the Sorbonne Nouvelle University HAL Complying with the FAIR principles all data underlying the results of the publications will be available under CC BY licence on Zenodo Each publication will be associated with a PDF file containing the analysis of the literary and film works mentioned in the article Data will be uploaded on Zenodo at the time of the preprint if possible otherwise at the moment of the publication Therefore the Data Management Plan will consist in a document describing the type of data that will be collected during the analysis of the literary and film works of the corpus and the methodology that will be used in order to process these data Moreover this document will describe in detail how the data underlying the results of the publications will be shared and made open curated and preserved</description>
